the end it turns out that showing/hiding annotation \"fields\" works well to make monochrome pixels, and keyboard input can be achieved by typing in a text input box.<p>All in all it's quite janky but a nice reminder of how general purpose PDF scripting can be. The linked PDF is all ASCII so you can just open it in a text editor, or have a look at the source code here: <a href=\"https://github.com/ThomasRinsma/pdftris/blob/main/gengrid.py\">https://github.com/ThomasRinsma/pdftris/blob/main/gengrid.py</a></p>\n<hr>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42645218\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42645218</a></p>\n<p>Points: 1240</p>\n<p># Comments: 218</p>\n","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"Luigi Mangione's account has been renamed on Stack Overflow","url":"https://substack.evancarroll.com/p/the-erasure-of-luigi-mangione","date":1736402558,"author":"OsrsNeedsf2P","unread":true,"content":"\n<p>Article URL: <a href=\"https://substack.evancarroll.com/p/the-erasure-of-luigi-mangione\">https://substack.evancarroll.com/p/the-erasure-of-luigi-mangione</a></p>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42642089\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42642089</a></p>\n<p>Points: 966</p>\n<p># Comments: 799</p>\n","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"I had to take down my course-swapping site or be expelled","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jdkaim_github-jdkaimhuskyswap-huskyswap-project-activity-7282609173316415488-1jdb","date":1736371632,"author":"jdkaim","unread":true,"content":"\n<p>Article URL: <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jdkaim_github-jdkaimhuskyswap-huskyswap-project-activity-7282609173316415488-1jdb\">https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jdkaim_github-jdkaimhuskyswap-huskyswap-project-activity-7282609173316415488-1jdb</a></p>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42638626\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42638626</a></p>\n<p>Points: 1331</p>\n<p># Comments: 691</p>\n","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"NeuralSVG: An Implicit Representation for Text-to-Vector Generation","url":"https://sagipolaczek.github.io/NeuralSVG/","date":1736360197,"author":"lnyan","unread":true,"content":"\n<p>Article URL: <a href=\"https://sagipolaczek.github.io/NeuralSVG/\">https://sagipolaczek.github.io/NeuralSVG/</a></p>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42636873\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42636873</a></p>\n<p>Points: 768</p>\n<p># Comments: 71</p>\n","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"Show HN: Atlas of Space","url":"https://atlasof.space/","date":1736347654,"author":"pieix","unread":true,"content":"\n<p>Hello HN! Sharing a recent side project of mine, the Atlas of Space, that I built out to explore the Solar System.<p>As a long-time space nerd, I realized recently that I didn't have a good intuition on the scale, speed, and relative orientation of the celestial bodies around us. So over the break I built out a kind of spatial Wikipedia to click around and learn about planets, moons, asteroids, and other bodies orbiting the Sun.<p>The physics is all simulated in the browser using simple Newtonian mechanics. There's a lot left to do from here, including modeling objects in non-Keplerian orbits and replaying different spacecraft missions.<p>Hope you have fun clicking around, and curious to hear what I should improve next!</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42634787\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42634787</a></p>\n<p>Points: 749</p>\n<p># Comments: 123</p>\n","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"Fidget","url":"https://www.mattkeeter.com/projects/fidget/","date":1736346658,"author":"todsacerdoti","unread":true,"content":"\n<p>Article URL: <a href=\"https://www.mattkeeter.com/projects/fidget/\">https://www.mattkeeter.com/projects/fidget/</a></p>\